# p1, p2, and p3 unify the closed definition #X & #Y, where #X embeds a field
# that closed #Y does not allow. They are equivalent up to field order and
# comprehension inlining, so "all" must fail with "field not allowed" on the
# disallowed field x in all three. The "not_bottom" comprehension filters out
# bottom list elements; whether it yields [] or propagates the error, and which
# positions "all" reports the error at, both depend on field order. See
# out/todo.txt.
-- in.cue --
// "all" evaluated before "not_bottom".
p1: {
	all: [#X & #Y] @test(err, code=eval, at=0.x, contains="field not allowed", pos=[3:4])
	not_bottom: [for x in all if x != _|_ {x}] @test(err, code=eval, contains="field not allowed")
	#X: {
		{x: "r"}
		...
	}
	#Y: k: "k"
}

// "not_bottom" evaluated before "all".
p2: {
	not_bottom: [for x in all if x != _|_ {x}] @test(eq, [])
	all: [#X & #Y] @test(err, code=eval, at=0.x, contains="field not allowed", pos=[-1:31, 2:4])
	#X: {
		{x: "r"}
		...
	}
	#Y: k: "k"
}

// "not_bottom" references the comprehension via a sibling field.
p3: {
	not_bottom: ref @test(eq, [])
	ref: [for x in all if x != _|_ {x}]
	all: [#X & #Y] @test(err, code=eval, at=0.x, contains="field not allowed", pos=[-1:24, 2:4])
	#X: {
		{x: "r"}
		...
	}
	#Y: k: "k"
}
-- out/todo.txt --
The results are not consistent across p1, p2, and p3, even though they differ
only in field order. p1 evaluates "all" before "not_bottom", so the comprehension
is not "forced" to run: the error is found directly on "all", which reports only
the disallowed field, and "not_bottom" propagates the error. p2 and p3 evaluate
the comprehension first, so it filters the failing element down to [] and also
contributes its own position to the "all" error.
Ideally, a future version of the evaluator would behave consistently regardless
of field order.
-- out/errors.txt --
[eval] p1.all.0.x: field not allowed:
    ./in.cue:6:4
[eval] p1.all.0.x: field not allowed:
    ./in.cue:6:4
[eval] p2.all.0.x: field not allowed:
    ./in.cue:14:31
    ./in.cue:17:4
[eval] p3.all.0.x: field not allowed:
    ./in.cue:26:24
    ./in.cue:29:4
